puts CodeHelpers.shitmorsetonumbers(ciphertext)
raise 'stop'
split = ciphertext.gsub('.','0').gsub('-','1').split(" ")

alpha_mod = ['abcde','fghik','lmnop','qrstu','vwxyz']

plaintext = []
l = split.count
p = 0
while p < split.count
  chr = split[p].to_i(2)-53
  if chr == 9
    p += 1
  elsif 0 <= chr && chr <= 4
    chr1 = split[p+1].to_i(2)-53
    plaintext << alpha_mod[chr][chr1] #polybius square
    p += 2
  else
    raise "how can this be... #{chr}"
  end
end

puts plaintext.join('')
=begin
to those who remain, what is there to say about these seven(looks knowingly into camera) that has not already been said?
their support has made our group what it is today.
it is with their support that we are able to be here today, to stand upon their shoulders and see all the path(looking again)ways in front of us.
we cannot forget their sacrifice, nor can we forget the charge they left to us all.
we must keep our eyes open and our hands(at this point just staring into camera) ready for whatever crosses our path.
as /he/ often said, "as the shadows grow long and the hours grow short, may they go in peace."
=end